<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-03T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-03T16:00:00-05:00" n="727" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d727">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 652.119/817</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Willard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-03T22:00:00+01:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 3, 1918, 10 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received May 5, 5.20
                                    p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1298. Embassy’s 1293, May 3, 9 p.m., War Trade Board 44 from
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_CTL1">Chadbourne</persName>. Embassy cannot support recommendations
                                therein contained. While terms of Spanish-American agreement of
                                March 7, 1918, have been technically violated in delay and otherwise
                                by Spanish Government, yet United States Government is securing and
                                accepting practically all the agreement calls for. Therefore to
                                notify Spanish Government that agreement is at end is serious step
                                and one to be taken only after great consideration and consultation
                                with French Government which is indirect party to contract. Moreover
                                such action would bring about immediate withdrawal of French credit.
                                This question also involves political policy and good faith. Embassy
                                requests instructions.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Willard</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>